The '''Amathus sarcophagus''' is a [[Cyprus|Cypriot]] [[sarcophagus]] that likely held a king of [[Amathus]]. Its sides show procession scenes, and typify Cypriot, Greek, and Near Eastern styles of the mid-fifth century BCE.

