[[File:Loza nemanjica.jpg|thumb|Nemanjić family tree from [[Visoki Dečani]] (ca. 1350).]]
The '''[[Nemanjić dynasty]]''' is depicted in a family tree [[Composition (visual arts)|composition]] in several specimen of [[Byzantine art]] [[fresco]]es in medieval [[Serbian Orthodox Church|Serbian Orthodox]] monasteries. The scheme is known as the '''Nemanjić family tree''' (''loza Nemanjića'').{{sfn|Vizantološki institut|2007|p=311}} Examples include those of [[Gračanica monastery|Gračanica]] (1321), [[Patriarchal Monastery of Peć|Peć]] (ca. 1335), [[Visoki Dečani]] (ca. 1350), and [[Matejče Monastery|Matejić]] (ca. 1360).{{sfn|Đurić|1978}}

The Nemanjić family tree is also preserved from engravings, such as those of Studenica (1733), and [[Hristofor Žefarović]] (1741).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.srpsko-nasledje.rs/sr-l/1998/05/article-10.html}}</ref>

